******** iPhone 4s Users on iOS 8.1 ********
We’re aware of a bug that is pushing the "Continue" button below the screen— please rest assured that we are working to fix this as soon as possible. In the meantime, visiting www.creditkarma.com, logging in, and continuing there will allow you to bypass the troublesome screen in the app. We apologize for this inconvenience and thank you for letting us know!

Best,
The Credit Karma Team


What's New:

• We’ve built in our Best Credit Cards feature. Now, you can explore our most popular credit cards right from the app.
• We’ve added a bottom navigation bar to your home screen to make getting around even easier.
• We’ve made general improvements to further perfect your experience.

description.standard:
Get your truly free credit score, credit report and credit monitoring with the Credit Karma app.

Become a member for free in-app and get your free credit score in just two minutes.

In its first week of launch, Credit Karma Mobile 
-Reached the #1 spot in financial apps 
-Reached the #7 spot in top free apps 
-Was given a 5-star rating by app users 

FEATURES

• Truly free credit scores
• Free credit reports
• Free credit monitoring
• Personalized recommendations
• Free membership. No credit card required.
• Safe and secure.

TESTIMONIALS FROM OUR MEMBERS

“Credit Karma helped me save over $3,000 on my credit card debt. It was quick and easy!” – James, MA

“My credit score has gone up 43 points in a single month after following some of their advice!” – Leslie, CA

CREDIT KARMA HAS BEEN FEATURED IN

• MSNBC
• SmartMoney
• USA TODAY
• TIME Moneyland
• TechCrunch

Credit Karma provides more than 30 million consumers with free credit scores and access to free credit monitoring to help them realize the everyday cost savings of having good credit by offering personalized savings recommendations for credit cards, student, auto, mortgage and home equity loans. It also provides financial education and access to free tools that empower consumers to take charge of their financial health including the free Credit Report Card, Credit Score Simulator and Credit Card Statistics. To learn more, visit www.creditkarma.com.
